relevant_findings.HEENT: Normocephalic/atraumatic, pupils equal, round, reactive to light and accommodation, extraocular movements intact, sclerae anicteric, mucous membranes moist, oropharynx clear
relevant_findings.neck: Supple, no thyromegaly, no jugular venous distention
relevant_findings.heart: Point of maximal impulse non-displaced, regular rate and rhythm, normal S1 and S2, no murmurs, rubs, or gallops
relevant_findings.lungs: Clear to auscultation bilaterally, no rales, rhonchi, or wheezes, good air movement, respiratory effort unlabored, no accessory muscle use
relevant_findings.abdomen: Normoactive bowel sounds, soft, non-tender, non-distended, no masses or hepatosplenomegaly, no rebound or guarding
relevant_findings.extremities: Warm, well perfused, no cyanosis, clubbing, or edema, 2+ peripheral pulses (radial and dorsalis pedis)
relevant_findings.neurological: Awake, alert and oriented to person, place, and time, cranial nerves II-XII grossly intact, muscle strength intact throughout, sensation grossly intact throughout, deep tendon reflexes 2+ and symmetric, cerebellar exam intact, steady gait
